{{Infobox ethnic group | group = Burun People | native_name = Burun | image = File:Sudan map1.png | population = 30,000 people 100,000 people (including separate groups) | languages = [[Burun language]] | religions = [[Islam]] [[Ethnic religions]] }}
'''Burun''' is an ethnic group of [[Sudan]] and [[South Sudan]]. They live in and around the Upper Nile Valley in Northern part of Maiwut State.They speak [[Burun language|Burun]], a [[Nilotic languages|Nilotic language]]. This ethnic group numbers about 8,000 persons, according to 2008 South Sudan'population sensus. Generally speaking, Burun people inhabitanted the areas present of Dajo, Pacime, Waldese and Kigile in Maiwut State....one of the 32.
== Society == The Burun speak the [[Burun language]]; a language in the [[Nilotic languages|Nilotic]] language family
