{{Infobox ethnic group |group = Filipinos in Greece |image = |pop = '''2,000''' (1996) |popplace = [[Athens]] |langs = [[Tagalog language|Tagalog]], [[English language|English]]; [[Greek language|Greek]] |rels = [[Roman Catholicism]], [[Greek Orthodox]] |related = [[Filipino people]], [[Overseas Filipinos]] }}
'''Filipinos in Greece''' consist of migrants from the [[Philippines]] to [[Greece]] and their descendants. According to official Greek statistics, there were 5,000 Filipinos in Greece in 1991, which declined to 2,000 by 1996. In reality, there were many more [[illegal immigrant|working in the country illegally]].<ref>{{harvnb|Iosifides|King|1999|p=193}}</ref><ref>{{citation|url=http://www.dole.gov.ph/news/details.asp?id=N000000739 |periodical=DOLE News |title=Imson urges Greece-based OFWs to take advantage of new legalization rules |date=2004-06-13 |accessdate=2009-10-23 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160123092632/http://www.dole.gov.ph/news/details.asp?id=N000000739 |archivedate=2016-01-23 |df= }}</ref> The Philippine community have set up a school for their children in downtown [[Athens]].<ref>{{harvnb|Cañete|2004|p=135}}</ref>
A large proportion are women (81% {{asof|1999|lc=on}}), who generally find employment as [[domestic worker]]s.<ref>{{harvnb|Iosifides|King|1999|p=194}}</ref> The association between Filipinas and domestic work is so strong that a Greek dictionary published in 1998 even defined "Filippineza", a term which literally means Filipina, to be "a domestic worker from the Philippines or a person who performs non-essential auxiliary tasks". Migrants and the Philippine [[Department of Foreign Affairs (Philippines)|Department of Foreign Affairs]] protested to the Greek government about the dictionary.<ref>{{citation|url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m0WDQ/is_1998_August_10/ai_53000395/?tag=content;col1|title=Philippines blasts 'Filipina' entry in Greek dictionary|date=1998-08-10|accessdate=2009-10-23|periodical=Kyodo News}} {{dead link|date=February 2011}}</ref>
